An Entity aids in the successful completion of a Purpose. Its Degree of utility may also be expressed. Some of the lexical units in this frame (e.g. great, good) can only express permanent, generic states of the Entity.

effective.a, excellent.a, fantastic.a, fine.a, good.a, great.a, ideal.a, ineffective.a, marvellous.a, outstanding.a, perfect.a, splendid.a, super.a, superb.a, terrific.a, tremendous.a, useful.a, utility.n, valuable.a, value.n, wonderful.a, work.v
